Its a place just to smoke hookah and relax. They do not serve alcoholic drinks here but do have some very good smoothies. Hookahs are always good. The flavor I always get is Supari Paan. I would have given it a 5, however my only concern is that when there is few people in the lounge the crew tends to relax a little too much snd just stay in the back and forget about your charcoal. Also they tend to favor people they know in the sense that they will tend to them more, as most businesses tend to treat a regular better. Wifi is free and quick. Music is mostly in arabic, which I do not mind. I just go there to smoke hookah and watch netflix. They have charging ports throughout as well and a backyard for the summer days.
